line_1: As if each India had been drain'd:
line_2: Now Show'rs of Gold and Gems are rain'd,

line_1: Was all from simple nature drain'd;
line_2: The little knowledge, I have gain'd,

line_1: Ye, who one bitter drop have drain'd
line_2: From slav'ry's cup, with horror stain'd,

line_1: Yet num'rous Vessels fill'd, before 'twas drain'd.
line_2: Whose Quantity of Oil one Pot contain'd;

line_1: Tho' each campaign she crowded nations drain'd,
line_2: And the fat soil with blood of thousands stain'd;

line_1: The Woods are travers'd; and the Lakes are drain'd:
line_2: To have the Honor of each Day sustain'd,
